<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🎨 Extra — CSS Colors &amp; Text Styling</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Selectors, Colors &amp; the Box Model · <strong>Course:</strong> Extra Worksheet · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>CSS picks a part of the page with a <strong>selector</strong>, then changes it with a <strong>property</strong> and a <strong>value</strong>. On paper you will read CSS, predict it, fix it, and explain it in your own words.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Keep these words handy: <strong>selector</strong>, <strong>property</strong>, <strong>value</strong>, <strong>padding</strong>, <strong>border</strong>, <strong>margin</strong>.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each snippet. Write what you think the page will look like.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;style&gt;
  h1 { color: blue; }
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;My Profile&lt;/h1&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What color is the heading? What does the <code>h1</code> before the <code>{</code> pick?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;style&gt;
  .note { background-color: #fef9c3; }
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;note&quot;&gt;Revise CSS selectors.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;note&quot;&gt;Practice the box model.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Feed the cat.&lt;/div&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>How many boxes turn yellow? Why?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;style&gt;
  h1 {
    font-size: 36px;
    text-align: center;
  }
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;My Study Notes&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today I learned about CSS.&lt;/p&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Which line moves to the middle of the page, the <code>h1</code> or the <code>p</code>? Why?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>Each snippet is broken. Read what it should do, then rewrite it so it works. Explain why the original was wrong.</p>
<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — This should turn the heading blue. Nothing changes.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">h1 { color blue; }
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> every property needs a <code>:</code> between it and its value.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug B</strong> — This should turn <code>&lt;div class="note"&gt;</code> yellow. It stays white.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">note { background-color: #fef9c3; }
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> a class selector starts with a dot.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug C</strong> — This should make the title 32 pixels tall. The size does not change.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">h1 { font-size: 32; }
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> a size needs a unit.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Explain the Code 📖</h2>
<p>This is the finished profile card from your lesson.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;style&gt;
  #card {
    width: 300px;
    background-color: #fff7ed;
    padding: 24px;
    border: 3px solid #f97316;
    margin: 40px auto;
  }
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;card&quot;&gt;
  &lt;h1&gt;Mina&lt;/h1&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Loves coding and cats.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</code></pre>
<table style="border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;max-width:460px;margin:16px auto;text-align:center;font-size:13px"><tr><td style="background:#fee2e2;padding:16px"><strong>margin</strong> — space outside<div style="border:4px solid #f97316;background:#fed7aa;margin-top:8px;padding:8px"><strong>border</strong> — the line<div style="background:#fff7ed;padding:16px;margin-top:8px"><strong>padding</strong> — space inside<div style="background:#ffffff;border:1px dashed #9ca3af;padding:12px;margin-top:8px"><strong>content</strong> — Mina</div></div></div></td></tr></table>

<p><strong>What does <code>#card</code> pick? How would <code>.card</code> be different?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong><code>padding: 24px</code> and <code>margin: 40px auto</code> both add space. Which space is inside the border?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>In <code>margin: 40px auto</code>, what does <code>auto</code> do to the card sideways?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

